title._content: Astronauts Sunita L. Williams, and Michael A. Lopez-Alegria don their extravehicular mobility unit space suits

description._content: Collection: NASA Human Spaceflight Collection General Description: International Space Station Imagery Description: ISS014-E-13528 (8 Feb. 2007) --- Astronauts Sunita L. Williams, flight engineer, and Michael A. Lopez-Alegria, commander and NASA ISS science officer, don their extravehicular mobility unit (EMU) space suits onboard the International Space Station prior to one of several Expedition 14 spacewalks. This marks the third extravehicular activity in nine days. image id: Photo-iss014e13528 UID: SPD-SPFLT-Photo-iss0 14e13528 original url: spaceflight.nasa.gov/gallery/images/station/crew-14/html/...
